### ‚ùå BUG 1 ‚Äî Backend VectorAI client missing `.connect()` 
`backend/main.py` line 450: `_get_vectorai_client()` creates the client but **never calls `.connect()`**. This is the same bug we fixed in `agents/shared/vectorai_client.py` yesterday. Without `.connect()`, all search calls from the Explorer will fail with "Client is not connected".

### ‚ùå BUG 2 ‚Äî CAM financial data garbage ‚Üí **NOT FIXED**
`seed_demo.py` is **completely unchanged**. It only patches 4 namespaces: `compliance`, `financials`, `risk`, `cam_output`. The `financials` namespace patch has:
- No `revenue_annual`, `ebitda_annual`, `interest_expense`, `principal_repayment` fields
- Only has `revenue_trend`, `ebitda_margin_pct`, `debt_service_coverage_ratio`

The doc-agent and bank-recon-agent extract the real financial data from PDFs, but since the uploaded PDF is just a sample, they produce garbage values (‚Çπ26.00 revenue, ‚Çπ0 debt).

